## tether Details (created 2026-03-13)

**Target:** `pexpect` (pexpect/pexpect) — Python process interaction with pseudo-terminals
- 149M downloads/month (#152 on PyPI), 2820 stars, 489 forks
- Two primary maintainers (takluyver, jquast), both inactive on features
- Last release v4.9 on 2023-11-25 (2+ years ago), previous v4.8 was 2020-01-17
- 165 open issues including: deprecated asyncio.coroutine (#677), Python 3.12 fork warnings (#817), ANSI leaks macOS 3.14 (#824), sendline leaking into .before (#821), bare excepts (#826)
- Depends on ptyprocess (also stale: last release 2020-12-28)
- No type annotations, no Tidelift, no funding
- ISC license

**Package name:** `tether` (verified available on PyPI)
**Python:** >= 3.10, zero dependencies (PTY handling built-in)

**Key differentiators:**
- Native async/await (not async_=True hack)
- Full type annotations — mypy/pyright strict clean
- Built-in PTY handling (no ptyprocess dependency)
- Context manager support (with/as)
- Fixes all known pexpect bugs (#677, #817, #821, #824, #826)
- SSH session helper
- PopenSpawn for Windows/pipe-based operation
- Drop-in pexpect compatibility shim

**5 phases:** Core PTY/Spawn/Expect → Advanced Features → Extensions (Async/SSH/Windows) → Quality/Compat → Docs/Release
**PM task #346** pending (priority 4).
**Journal entries:** #538 (research), #539 (rejected candidates), #540 (decision).

